 MBOMBELA – Capt Richard Nkwanyana appeared in the Nelspruit Magistrates Court on charges of theft and defeating the ends of justice on Monday. He was arrested on Monday, after handing himself over to the Hawks’ Middelburg unit following a drawn-out investigation into the alleged theft of approximately R439 900, the Hawks said in a statement. He was released on R5 000 bail and has been barred from entering any Hawks offices. He is expected to return to court again on October 17.    